Hassan spoke for his father in audiences with strangers, as he did for the adventurers that ultimately released Martek.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|66}}

Hassan did not spend much time in his tent after his bride was kidnapped, and only returned at night to sleep.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|71}} Despite this change in his own attitude, he was concerned that his brother Korus had lately never attended the offering for the holy days, and was staying by himself.

According to [[Hogan Underwood]], Hassan had been in the bar at the time of his bride's disappearance.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|72}} Hassan wandered the oasis sometimes.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|67}}
